text: George Vincent Rhoden (13 December 1926 - 24 August 2024)Biography and Statistics at Sports Reference was a Jamaican athlete. He was the winner of two Olympic gold medals in 1952. He was born in Kingston. Rhoden died on 24 August 2024 in Kingston at the age of 97. ==References== Category:1926 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Jamaican sprinters Category:Sportspeople from Kingston, Jamaica Category:Olympians for Jamaica Category:Olympic gold medalists
